Introduction¶

Dataset contains 10,866 rows, 21 columns (id,imdb_id,popularity, budget, revenue,.. ), Also, the dataset contains null_values that must be handle with them by drop or filling, and there are columns separated by a delimiter that must be separated to extract important information from them, such as a column(cast,genres)

Questions for Analysis:¶

1) Movies that make profits $1Billion or more.
2) who are top 10 cast?
3) what are top 10 popularity movies?
4) Movies with high and low vote_average
5) what is the number of movies for each Genre?
6) Movies that have revenues 10 times their budget.
7) what is the profit in each release year?
8) Any features dependent on each other ?
9) Visualization between two high features

Function return 10 top movies¶

In [42]:
#this function return top 10 movies depend on given column
def top_10_movie(column):
    top_movies = movie.sort_values(by=[column],ascending=False).head(10)
    return top_movies[['original_title',column]]

I noticed that some feature dependent on each other such that (Revenue , profit_movie), (Revenue , Budget),(popularity , Revenue), (popularity , profit_movie), (profit_movie , Budget) and (Budget , popularity) > 0.5 and others features are weak dependent(independent) < 0.5.¶

Visualization Strong features that depend on each other¶

(Revenue , profit_movie) are more features strong positive dependent with 98%¶

Conclusions:¶

Results After analyzing the data, found that:¶

1) Jurassic World movie make profits more than 1 Billion.
2) Robert De Niro is More cast in movies.
3) Jurassic World is most popularity movie.
4) (The Story of Film: An Odyssey) is The movie with high the vote average.
5) (Manos: The Hands of Fate) is The movie with low the vote average.
6) Most of the movies are of the Drama genre So I recommend making more movies of this genre.
7) 2015 is the highest Release year of movies profits.
8) (Revenue,Profit Movie):The two highest features positively depend on each other Therefore, the production of high-Revenues Movies must always be increased to increase the profits.

Limitation:¶

1) the Budget and Revenue column do not have currency unit, It is possible that it has a different currency according to the country in which the movie was produced, as this affects the budget and revenues.
2) There are Null values and 0 have lost some important information.
3) Due to the presence of null values and droping them, this will certainly have an impact on the analysis process.
4) The genre column had to be separated because the result took a lot of time, so it was necessary to separate and clean it before the analysis.
